http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/KPCC%E2%80%99s-State-wide-march-to-be-flagged-off-on-Monday/article13976470.ece

With the aim to streamline its organisational set-up ahead of the Assembly elections, the Kerala Pradesh Congress Committee’s (KPCC) State-wide march will be flagged off from Kumbla near here on January 4.The Jana Raksha March captained by KPCC president V.M. Sudheeran will be flagged off on Monday evening. Chief Minister Oommen Chandy will hand over the party flag to Mr. Sudheeran at the function to be presided over by former KPCC chief Ramesh Chennithala.“The march, the second of its kind led by Mr. Sudheeran, is being taken out to highlight the need to safeguard secular values, to empower youth and to usher in comprehensive development in the State,” District Congress Committee president C.K. Sreedharan told a press conference here on Friday.AICC general secretary Mukul Wasnik, who holds the charge of party affairs in the State, would deliver the keynote address at the function, to be attended by senior party leaders from Kerala and Karnataka, he said.On the inaugural day, the march will conclude with a public meeting at Cherkala at 6 p.m. Mr. Sudheeran will address public meetings at Chattamchal, Kanhangad and Thirkaripur before the march enters Kannur district.The march, which would culminate in Thiruvananthapuram on February 9 after touching all 140 Assembly segments, would focus on the prevailing national political scenario, the achievements made by the Oommen Chandy government, the dangers of political violence, the campaign against liquor and drugs, waste management, women empowerment and organic vegetable cultivation, he added.The Jana Raksha March will culminate in the Capital on February 9.